**In [2]:**

{% highlight python %}
def divisors(n):
    return [x for x in range(2, n//2+1) if n % x == 0]
{% endhighlight %}

**In [3]:**

{% highlight python %}
N=10000
rangon = range(1,N)
d = []
p = []
s = []
for i in rangon:
    d_ = divisors(i)
    p_ = list(primefac.primefac(i))
    d.append( d_ )
    p.append( p_ )
    s.append( list(set(p_)))
{% endhighlight %}

**In [4]:**

{% highlight python %}
df = pd.DataFrame()
df['sumdivisors'] = list(map(sum,d))
df['ndivisors'] = list(map(len,d))
df['nuniquefactors'] = list(map(len,s))
df['sumuniquefactors'] = list(map(sum,s))
df['sumfactors'] = list(map(sum,p))
df['nfactors'] = list(map(len,p))
df.index=rangon
{% endhighlight %}
 
 

**In [14]:**

{% highlight python %}
primos = array(primefac.primes(N))
figure(figsize=(7,7))
c = np.zeros(len(rangon))
c[primos-1] = 1
c[1::2] = 2
x = array([0,N])
plot(x,x,'k',alpha=0.5)
# plot(x,x/5.,'k',alpha=0.5)

cmap=['r','b','g']
labels = ['Rest','Primes','Even']

for i in [2,1,0]:
    ix = c==i
    semilogy(df.sumdivisors[ix],df.sumfactors[ix],'o',color=cmap[i],alpha=0.1,markeredgecolor='none',label=labels[i]);

xlim(-N*0.01,N)
ylim(-N*0.01,N)
xlabel('Sum of divisors')
ylabel('Sum of factors');
leg = legend();
for lh in leg.legendHandles: lh._legmarker.set_alpha(1);

from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf

figure()
x = (df.sumdivisors+1)/df.index
df['normsumdiv'] = x
plot(x)
ylabel('Normalized sum of divisors')

plot_acf(x,lags=400)
